# Pet Circle — Screen Completion Guide

## How to Use This File

This is a checklist of every gap in the app UI. When working on a screen, consult the relevant section below to see exactly what needs fixing. Each item lists the file, the problem, and the required fix.

Stores are documented in the `state-management.mdc` rule file.

---

## Priority 1 — Core Data Flow

### Measurement Screen (`lib/screens/measurement/measurement_screen.dart`)

| Status | Item | Details |
|--------|------|---------|
| WORKS | Tap counter with haptics | Scale animation, count increments |
| WORKS | Timer (15/30/60s) and BPM calculation | Result dialog shown correctly |
| WORKS | "Measure Again" button | Resets timer and closes dialog |
| BROKEN | "Add to Graph" button | Line ~299: `// TODO: Add the measurement to the graph` — no save logic |
| PLACEHOLDER | VisionRR mode tab | Just an icon and description text — no camera/processing |

**Required fixes:**
- Wire "Add to Graph" to `measurementStore.addMeasurement(petName, measurement)`
- After saving, show success feedback and optionally navigate to trends
- VisionRR: leave as placeholder for now (Phase 3 feature)

### Trends Screen (`lib/screens/trends/trends_screen.dart`)

| Status | Item | Details |
|--------|------|---------|
| WORKS | Tab switching (Overview, History, Medication) | Local state |
| WORKS | Period dropdown (24h, 3d, 7d, etc.) | Changes local state |
| HARDCODED | SRR chart data | Uses static `_SrrPoint` list (Jan 3–9) — not from measurement store |
| BROKEN | Measurement History "Export" | `onExport: () {}` — empty callback |
| PARTIAL | Medication export | Shows CSV dialog + snackbar, but does not write a file |
| BROKEN | Add medication "Save" | Closes sheet; form data not captured or persisted |
| HARDCODED | `'Princess • 7 recordings'` | Line ~555: hardcoded pet name and count |

**Required fixes:**
- Replace `_SrrPoint` data with `measurementStore.getMeasurements(petName)`
- Wire Export button to show export dialog (CSV preview like medication does)
- Wire Add Medication Save to `medicationStore.addMedication(...)`
- Derive pet name and recording count from stores

### Onboarding (`lib/screens/onboarding/onboarding_step1.dart` – `step4.dart`)

| Status | Item | Details |
|--------|------|---------|
| WORKS | Page navigation and step order | Flow controller works |
| NOT PERSISTED | Step 1: name, breed, age, photo | Input stored in local state only; lost on completion |
| NOT PERSISTED | Step 2: diagnosis dropdown | Selection not saved |
| NOT PERSISTED | Step 3: target respiratory rate | Local state only |
| BROKEN | Step 4: "Add to Care Circle" | Shows snackbar + clears email; no invite logic |
| WORKS | Step 4: "Complete" navigates to dashboard | Navigation works |

**Required fixes:**
- Collect all step data into a pet creation model
- On completion, call `petStore.addPet(newPet)` to persist the new pet
- Care circle invite: add member to the pet's care circle (mock — just show success)

